1 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
2 Sec. 1. FINDINGS
3 The General Assembly finds that:
4 (1) Lake Memphremagog is of integral importance to Vermont and
5 Quebec as the lake:
6 (A) is the largest body of water in northeastern Vermont and
7 southeastern Quebec;
8 (B) provides over 175,000 people with drinking water; and
9 (C) is an important economic driver in northeastern Vermont and
10 southeastern Canada, drawing people and resources for its beautiful landscapes
11 and numerous recreational opportunities.
12 (2) Phosphorus runoff is causing or contributing to excessive algal
13 biomass in Lake Memphremagog, impairing the swimming and aesthetic uses
14 of the lake.
15 (3) Phosphorus runoff to Lake Memphremagog is contributing to the
16 more frequent cyanobacteria outbreaks in the lake, which pose threats to public
17 health and natural resources.
18 (4) Vermont must take responsibility for the impairments to Lake
19 Memphremagog as:
20 (A) more than 100 permanent or intermittent tributaries feed Lake
21 Memphremagog, with 71 percent of the watershed located in Vermont; and
