1 Sec. 3. 10 V.S.A. § 1310 is amended to read:
2 § 1310. DESIGNATION OF LAKE IN CRISIS
3 (a) The Secretary of Natural Resources (Secretary) shall review whether a
4 lake in the State should be designated as a lake in crisis upon the Secretary’s
5 own motion or upon petition of 15 or more persons or a selectboard of a
6 municipality in which the lake or a portion of the lake is located.
7 (b) The Secretary shall designate a lake as a lake in crisis if, after review
8 under subsection (a) of this section, the Secretary determines that:
9 (1) the lake or segments of the lake have been listed as impaired; and
10 (2) the condition of the lake will cause:
11 (A) a potential harm to the public health; and
12 (B) a risk of damage to the environment or natural resources; and.
13 (3) a municipality in which the lake or a portion of the lake is located
14 has reduced the valuation of real property due to the condition of the lake.
15 [Repealed.]
16 Sec. 4. 10 V.S.A. § 1311(c) is amended to read:
17 (c) Term of designation. A lake shall remain designated as in crisis under
18 this section until the Secretary determines that the lake no longer satisfies the
19 criteria for designation under subsection 1310(b) of this section title.
